text: Seacat may refer to: * Seacat missile, a short-range surface-to-air missile system * SeaCat (1992–2004), ferry company formerly operating from between Northern Ireland, Scotland and England * The Sea-Cat, an imaginary monster from Flann O'Brien's novel An Béal Bocht * Atlantic wolffish * Sandra Seacat (born 1936), American actress and acting coach
title: Seacat
